# NIX DEVELOP
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Run a shell with the development environment of a flake.
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix develop: Enter the devShell defined in the current flake.

### Essentials
- nix develop .#my-shell: Enter a specific devShell.
- nix develop -c zsh: Enter the devShell using a specific shell instead of default.

### Intermediaries
- nix develop --command make build: Run a build command inside the dev environment.

### Advanceds
- nix develop --ignore-environment: Enter a completely clean environment.

### Uncommons
- nix develop --redirect <url> <path>: Redirect a dependency to a local path.

## Tips
- Sets up environment variables (like CFLAGS, PATH) defined in devShells.

## Disclaimers
- Can be slow if dependencies need to be built/downloaded.

## Alternatives
- direnv: Automatically load nix develop environments when entering a directory.

